# Wazuh Manager: Installation & Credential Troubleshooting

## Project Phase: Management Layer Deployment
The Wazuh Manager serves as the central "Brain" of the SOC Lab, responsible for indexing logs, triggering alerts, and managing endpoint agents.

---

## 🛠️ Installation Procedure
The manager was deployed on a hardened **Ubuntu 24.04 LTS** instance using the official Wazuh All-in-One assistant.

* **Specifications:** 2 vCPU, 8GB RAM, 50GB SSD.
* **Network:** Static IP `192.168.1.102` on the isolated `SOC-LAN`.
* **Deployment Command:**
  ``` bash
  curl -sO [https://packages.wazuh.com/4.14/wazuh-install.sh](https://packages.wazuh.com/4.14/wazuh-install.sh) && sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a
```

---

## 🕵️ Troubleshooting Log: Authentication Sync Failure

### 🚩 Incident
**Issue:** After a successful "All-in-One" installation, the generated `admin` credentials were consistently rejected by the Wazuh Dashboard with an "Invalid username or password" error.

**Analysis:** This indicated a synchronization gap between the **Wazuh Indexer** (the database holding the security hashes) and the **Wazuh Dashboard** (the UI attempting to authenticate). Standard service restarts did not resolve the discrepancy.

---

### 🛠️ The Fix: Out-of-Band Credential Override
To resolve the sync failure, I bypassed the UI and utilized the back-end security utility to force-update the cryptographic hashes in the indexer database.

**Technical Challenges Overcome:**
1. **Binary Location:** The utility was not in the system's global `$PATH`. I located it within the indexer plugin directory.
2. **Syntax Precision:** Identified and corrected a pathing error (correcting `wazuh-passwords-tools` to the singular `wazuh-passwords-tool.sh`).

**Command Executed:**
```bash
sudo bash /usr/share/wazuh-indexer/plugins/opensearch-security/tools/wazuh-passwords-tool.sh -u admin -p [REDACTED_SECURE_PASSWORD]
```
