# Windows 11 Agent Deployment

## Objective
To establish a secure telemetry link between the Windows 11 Enterprise Workstation and the Wazuh Manager for real-time log collection and endpoint monitoring.

## Deployment Procedure

### 1. Agent Configuration
Using the Wazuh Dashboard's Agent Deployment Wizard, the following parameters were defined:
* **Target OS:** Windows 11
* **Manager IP:** `192.168.1.102`
* **Agent Name:** `Win11-Workstation-01`

### 2. Installation via PowerShell
The agent was installed using an elevated PowerShell session to ensure proper registry permissions and service registration.

**Command Executed:**
```powershell
# Commands provided by Wazuh Deployment Wizard
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri [https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/windows/wazuh-agent-4.x.msi](https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/windows/wazuh-agent-4.x.msi) -OutFile ${env:tmp}\wazuh-agent.msi; msiexec.exe /i ${env:tmp}\wazuh-agent.msi /q WAZUH_MANAGER='192.168.1.102' WAZUH_AGENT_NAME='Win11-Workstation-01'

# Manually starting the service
NET START Wazuh

